PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY

FHR's policy is to pursue continuous improvement through the use of tools such as follows: 

- Revisions to the Management of Change process;

- Process Hazard Analyses (PHAs), which is to incorporate requirements identified in the National Emphasis Program (NEP);

- Mechanical Integrity provisions;

- Internal and third party compliance audits;

- An ongoing dialogue with the FHR, RTFC and the local LEPC.

PROCESS UNIT PROGRAM LEVEL CERTIFICATION

The FHR West Refinery certification statement and signatory as required by 40 CFR 68.12(b)(4) and 40 CFR 68.185(b) is being provided electronically via RMP*eSubmit.
